    • Method Detail

      • arrayObjectNewBuilder

        JCGLArrayObjectBuilderType arrayObjectNewBuilder()
                                          throws JCGLException
        Retrieve a new array object builder. The returned builder can be used indefinitely but is tied to the JCGLContextType upon which it was created.
        Returns:
        A new array object builder
        Throws:
        JCGLException - On OpenGL errors

      • arrayObjectNewBuilderFromObject

        JCGLArrayObjectBuilderType arrayObjectNewBuilderFromObject(JCGLArrayObjectUsableType o)
        Parameters:
        o - An array object
        Returns:
        A new array object builder, initialized to the values used to construct o
        See Also:
        arrayObjectNewBuilder()

      • arrayObjectAllocate

        JCGLArrayObjectType arrayObjectAllocate(JCGLArrayObjectBuilderType b)
                                 throws JCGLException

        Allocate and bind an array object based on the values given in b.

        Calling this method will unbind any currently bound array buffer.

        Calling this method will unbind any currently bound array object.

        Parameters:
        b - The array object builder
        Returns:
        A new array object
        Throws:
        JCGLException - On OpenGL errors
        See Also:
        JCGLArrayBuffersType.arrayBufferUnbind()

      • arrayObjectGetCurrentlyBound

        JCGLArrayObjectUsableType arrayObjectGetCurrentlyBound()
                                                throws JCGLException
        Returns:
        The currently bound array object, or arrayObjectGetDefault() if the user has not bound an array object.
        Throws:
        JCGLException - Iff an OpenGL error occurs

      • arrayObjectBind

        void arrayObjectBind(JCGLArrayObjectUsableType a)
              throws JCGLException,
                     JCGLExceptionDeleted
        Bind the given array object.
        Parameters:
        a - The array object
        Throws:
        JCGLException - Iff an OpenGL error occurs
        JCGLExceptionDeleted - Iff the given array object has already been deleted

      • arrayObjectUnbind

        void arrayObjectUnbind()
                throws JCGLException
        Unbind the current array object. If no object is bound, this call has no effect.
        Throws:
        JCGLException - Iff an OpenGL error occurs

      • arrayObjectDelete

        void arrayObjectDelete(JCGLArrayObjectType a)
                throws JCGLException,
                       JCGLExceptionDeleted,
                       JCGLExceptionObjectNotDeletable

        Deletes the object referenced by a.

        Calling this method will unbind a iff it is bound.

        Parameters:
        a - The array buffer
        Throws:
        JCGLExceptionDeleted - If the object is already deleted
        JCGLException - Iff an OpenGL error occurs
        JCGLExceptionObjectNotDeletable - Iff the object is the default array object
        See Also:
        arrayObjectGetDefault()

      • arrayObjectGetDefault

        JCGLArrayObjectUsableType arrayObjectGetDefault()
        A default array object is provided in order to allow for code to create and manipulate JCGLIndexBufferType values without needing to explicitly create an array object just for this purpose.
        Returns:
        A reference to the default array object
